emuInput.TitMainTitle: Portrait of Eugene Robinson wearing dark shirt, standing in interior
emuInput.CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 6, 1956, pg. 1, reads: "Stabbing Victim - Fifteen-year-old Eugene Robinson, of 2515 1/2 Charles St., North Side, shown in two poses above, was stabbed in the back, after the Fifth Ave. - North Catholic football game at Oliver High School field, by a switchblade wielded by Bernard Gerlach, also a North Side student. - Harris Photo."
